comment_data.body:
This is rather a candidate for inlining than for exporting. It's really just a short wrapper around `PyDict_GetItemWithError()` in most cases.
```suggestion
/////////////// dict_getitem_default.proto ///////////////
```
comment_data.diff_hunk:
@@ -198,7 +198,7 @@ static PyObject* __Pyx__PyList_PopIndex(PyObject* L, PyObject* py_ix, Py_ssize_t
 #endif
 
 
-/////////////// dict_getitem_default.proto ///////////////
+/////////////// dict_getitem_default.export ///////////////

comment_data.body: Hang on â€“ we do not rely on this for importing the shared module code, do we? :)
I checked that an I think not.
Thanks for checking. I was only half serious on this, but it's obviously something we need to take care of. Good to have tests.
